%N A066998 a(0)=0; a(n) = n^2*a(n-1) + 1.
%C A066998 if s(n) is a sequence defined as s(0)=x, s(n) = n^2*s(n-1) + k, then s(n) = n!^2*x + a(n)*k. - _Gary Detlefs_, Feb 20 2010
